Ethyle Cooke https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethyle_Cooke 0 Ethyle Cooke (4 August 1885 - 20 April 1949) was an American silent film actress of the 1910s. In 1915, she married another prominent silent film actor of the time, Harry Benham. Cooke starred in many popular movies, such as A Small Town Girl, Stronger than Death, and The Fugitive.
